05/02/2004
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- A family of three became the first Serb refugees to return to Pristina on Wednesday (4 February). They were joined by a Serb woman who will stay with them until she can move to her own home. The returns were organised by UNMIK and the Danish Refugee Council.
In other news, a UN court postponed until 10 February the trial of Shefqet Musliu, a former commander of the self-styled ethnic Albanian Liberation Army of Presevo, Medvedja and Bujanovac, a group once active in southern Serbia. Musliu is accused of kidnapping, attempted extortion, unlawful possession of weapons and criminal association. (AFP - 04/02/04)
